Description: Double handle of Koan pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; club symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.59, 28. Name, Heroidas. Parallels known from Alexandria, Kos and Abdera.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0112)
